               <msItem n="1" xml:id="a1">
                  <locus from="1a" to="1a">Fol. 1a</locus>
                  <title ref="" type="supplied">Index to the lessons</title>
                  <rubric xml:lang="syr"><locus from="1a" to="1a"/>ܦܘܪܫ ܩܪ̈ܝܢܐ</rubric>
                 <note>One reader has prefixed to the volume an index. It is drawn up in the ordinary form, <choice><abbr><foreign xml:lang="syr">ܟـ</foreign> standing for </abbr><expan><foreign xml:lang="syr">ܟܘܪܣܐ</foreign></expan></choice>, quire, and <choice><abbr><foreign xml:lang="syr">ܦ</foreign> for </abbr><expan><foreign xml:lang="syr">ܦܬܚܐ</foreign></expan></choice>, opening or interstice; e.g.</note>
                  <note><quote xml:lang="syr"><locus from="1a" to="1a"/>
                     <table>
                        <row>
                           <cell>܀ܩ܀ ܕܚܕܒܫܒܐ: ܟܚ : ܟـ : ܕ : ܦ : ܛ :</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <cell>܀ܩ܀ ܕܚܕܒܫܒܐ : ܟܛ : ܟـ : ܗ : ... : ... : </cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <cell>܀ܩ܀ ܕܚܕܒܫܒܐ : ܠ : ܟـ : ܗ : ܦ : ܐ :</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <cell>܀ܩ܀ ܕܚܕܒܫܒܐ : ܠܐ : ܟـ : ܘ : ܦ : ܗ : ܘ܏ܫ. </cell>
                        </row>
                     </table>
                  </quote></note>
               </msItem>
               <msItem n="2" xml:id="a2">
                  <locus from="2b" to="200b">Foll. 2b-200b</locus>
                  <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/71" type="supplied">The four Gospels according to the Peshitta version</title>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="b1">
                     <locus from="2b" to="57">Foll. 2b-57</locus>
                     <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/72" type="supplied">Matthew</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="4" xml:id="b2">
                     <locus from="57a" to="93b">Foll. 57a-93b</locus>
                     <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/73" type="supplied">Mark</title>
                     <finalRubric xml:lang="syr"><locus from="93b" to="93b"/>ܫܠܡ ܐܘܢܓܠܝܘܢ ܩܕܝܫܐ ܟܪܘܙܘܬܐ ܕܡܪܩܘܣ. ܕܡܠ̣ܠ ܪܗܘܡܐܝܬ ܒܪܗܘܡܐ ܡܕܝܢܬܐ. ܘܗ̣ܘ ܝܬ݂ܒ ܐܦܣܩܘܦܐ ܩܕܡܝܐ ܒܐܠܟܣܢܕܪܝܐ ܪܒܬܐ.</finalRubric>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="5" xml:id="b3">
                     <locus from="94a" to="154b">Foll. 94a-154b</locus>
                     <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/74" type="supplied">Luke</title>
                     <finalRubric xml:lang="syr"><locus from="154b" to="154b"/><sic>ܫܠܡ ܐܘܢܓܠܝܘܢ ܩܕܝܫܐ. ܟܪܘܙܘܬܐ ܕܠܘܩܐ.ܕܡܠܠ ܝܘܢܐܝܬ ܒܐܦܣܘܣ</sic></finalRubric>
                     <note>The letters  <quote xml:lang="syr">ܦܣܘܣ</quote> have, however, been partially erased.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="6" xml:id="b4">
                     <locus from="154b" to="200b">Foll. 154b-200b</locus>
                     <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/75" type="supplied">John</title>
                     <colophon><ref target="#addition4">See additions.</ref></colophon>
                  </msItem>
                  <note>The Ammonian sections and Eusebian canons are marked in the text, and there is a harmony at the foot of each page.</note>
                 <note>The lessons are rubricated in the text in the usual way.</note>
               </msItem>
